## 🔄 RTL Layout Support
### CSS Direction Handling
- Use Tailwind's built-in RTL support
- Add `dir="rtl"` to HTML elements when `lang === 'ar'`
- Use logical properties: `ms-` (margin-start), `me-` (margin-end)
- Avoid hardcoded `left`/`right` - use `start`/`end` instead

### Icon and Layout Mirroring
- Mirror directional icons (arrows, etc.) for Arabic
- Ensure proper text alignment: `text-right` for Arabic, `text-left` for English
- Handle form layouts and navigation appropriately

## 🎯 Cultural Considerations
- Green, white, and gold color scheme aligns with Saudi cultural preferences
- Use respectful and professional Arabic terminology
- Consider Islamic calendar dates where relevant
- Ensure currency display uses Saudi Riyal (ر.س / SAR)

## 📱 SEO & Metadata
As seen in [src/pages/Index.tsx](mdc:src/pages/Index.tsx):
- Update page titles dynamically based on language
- Provide Arabic meta descriptions
- Include structured data in both languages